Package: openmortal
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, ${perl:Depends}, openmortal-data (= ${binary:Version})
Description:
 OpenMortal is a free, open-source fighting game — a humorous parody and spiritual successor of the classic arcade fighter Mortal Kombat.
 The game currently offers around 16–18 playable characters (with potential for more), and even allows players to create their own character.
 Multiplayer is the focus — you can fight against friends locally or over the network.
 Because OpenMortal is released under the GPL, its full source code and assets are freely available: one can study, modify, and redistribute them according to the license.

Package: openmortal-data
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: OpenMortal – data files
 This is required data files for OpenMortal. OpenMortal is a free, open-source fighting game — a humorous parody and spiritual successor of the classic arcade fighter Mortal Kombat.
 The game currently offers around 16–18 playable characters (with potential for more), and even allows players to create their own character.
 Multiplayer is the focus — you can fight against friends locally or over the network.
 Because OpenMortal is released under the GPL, its full source code and assets are freely available: one can study, modify, and redistribute them according to the license.
